WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.620
Welcome back. In this lesson, we will install the MCP plugins for x64dbg.

00:00:07.260 --> 00:00:14.040
I assume you already have x64dbg installed. If you haven't, then just go ahead and install it first.

00:00:14.500 --> 00:00:16.180
Then, continue with this lesson.

00:00:17.200 --> 00:00:21.500
Now, we will install the MCP server for x64dbg.

00:00:22.020 --> 00:00:26.980
Go to this GitHub. You can just google for Agent Smithers MCP server.

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:29.240
Then, click on the releases link.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.680
Download both ZIP files and unzip them.

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:39.760
On the left is the location of the releases folder for the installed x64dbg on my PC.

00:00:40.340 --> 00:00:41.840
Just look for it on your PC.

00:00:42.400 --> 00:00:44.860
On the right are the unzipped files you downloaded.

00:00:45.540 --> 00:00:48.980
On the left, open the plugins folder for x32.

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:52.800
If the plugins folder does not exist, you may create it.

00:00:53.260 --> 00:00:59.720
On the right, open the x32dbg x86 subfolders until you see all the plugin files.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.320
Then, copy all the files to the plugins folder on the left.

00:01:04.220 --> 00:01:07.960
Now, repeat the same thing for the 64-bit version.

00:01:08.700 --> 00:01:11.780
On the left, open the plugin folder for x64.

00:01:12.280 --> 00:01:14.400
If there is none, just create it.

00:01:14.980 --> 00:01:21.800
On the right, open the x64dbg x64 subfolders until you see all the plugin files.

00:01:22.260 --> 00:01:25.440
Then, just copy and paste it into the plugins folder on the left.

00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:30.440
Right-click on X32DBG and run as administrator.

00:01:30.440 --> 00:01:39.440
Click on the Log tab and check to confirm that MCP server is listening on port 50300.

00:01:39.440 --> 00:01:47.440
If it fails to start on port 50300, it could be because another process is already running on that port.

00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:54.440
If your MCP server fails to start because of port 50300 conflicts,

00:01:54.440 --> 00:01:57.480
Just follow the instructions on this page to solve the problem.

00:01:59.320 --> 00:02:04.760
To confirm that MCP server has started, open the CMD line terminal and type the

00:02:04.760 --> 00:02:12.360
netstat find string command as shown here. You should see port 50300 is in a listening state.

00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:19.000
Do the same thing for x64 dbg, right click and run as administrator.

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:26.600
Similarly, click on the log tab and check to make sure MCP server is listening on port 50300

00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:32.020
and also repeat the netstat find string command in the CMD line terminal

00:02:32.020 --> 00:02:38.080
Next, download the practice crackme zip file from the resource section for this lesson

00:02:38.080 --> 00:02:42.860
The unzip password is www.crackinglessons.net

00:02:43.020 --> 00:02:47.880
We will be using these crackmes to test OpenClaw in later lessons in this course

00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:49.980
That's all for this video.

00:02:49.980 --> 00:02:50.980
Thank you for watching.

